  "insights": {
    "title": "Insights on Children Aged 12 to 23 Months - Vaccination Status",
    "subtitle": "Long-form analysis of completion and no-vaccination patterns across regions and background characteristics.",
    "overview": "The national profile improved between 2022 and 2025, but the most important story is how uneven that progress is across places and groups. Basic-antigen coverage rose from 71.8 to 77.1, full national-schedule coverage rose from 59.4 to 62.4, and the share with no vaccinations fell from 11.2 to 5.7. At the same time, regional differences remain wide: in 2025, full-schedule coverage ranges from 13.0 in BARMM to 94.3 in Ilocos Region, and no-vaccination ranges from 0.0 in Ilocos and NIR to 28.1 in BARMM.",
    "sections": [
      {
        "heading": "National gains are real, but not evenly distributed",
        "body": "At the country level, all three status measures moved in the right direction from 2022 to 2025. Basic-antigen completion increased by 5.3 points, full-schedule completion increased by 3.0 points, and no-vaccination fell by 5.5 points. This is a meaningful shift, but subgroup and regional patterns show that progress did not come at the same pace everywhere."
